- 'Most populous precincts' refers to precincts with a population greater than 10,000;
- 'Democratic candidates' refers to candidates from the 'Democrat' party.

- "blossomed with voter engagement" refers to precincts with a voter turnout percentage higher than the average turnout percentage;
- "bloom of voter participation" refers to the average voter turnout percentage across all precincts;
- Voter turnout percentage is calculated as (total ballots cast / registered voters) * 100.

